"script": "In one of the driest deserts on Earth, where it can go years without rain, the kangaroo rat thrives without ever taking a single drink. You see, it pulls nearly all its water from the dry seeds it eats. Its body chemically breaks those seeds down and squeezes the moisture out of them. Then it locks that water in, with kidneys so powerful its urine comes out almost as a paste. It even seals itself in a cool burrow by day to avoid losing a breath of moisture. This means it can outlast a camel in the desert.",
